sca.check.remediation: Edit or create a file ending in *.conf in the /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/ directory or the /etc/ssh/sshd_config file and set the MaxStartups parameter as follows: MaxStartups 10:30:60 Run the following command to comment out any MaxStartups parameter entries in files ending in *.conf in the /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/ directory or the /etc/ssh/sshd_config file that include any setting greater than 10:30:60: # grep -Pi '^\\s*maxstartups\\s+(((1[1-9]|[1-9][0-9][0-9]+):([0-9]+):([0-9]+))|(([0-9]+):(3[1-9]|[4-9][0-9]|[1-9][0-9][0-9]+):([0-9]+))|(([0-9]+):([0-9]+):(6[1-9]|[7-9][0-9]|[1-9][0-9][0-9]+)))' /etc/ssh/sshd_config /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/*.conf | while read -r l_out; do sed -ri \"/^\\s*MaxStartups\\s+(((1[1-9]|[1-9][0-9][0-9]+):([0-9]+):([0-9]+))|(([0-9]+):(3[1-9]|[4-9][0-9]|[1-9][0-9][0-9]+):([0-9]+))|(([0-9]+):([0-9]+):(6[1-9]|[7-9][0-9]|[1-9][0-9][0-9]+)))/s/^/# /\" \"$(awk -F: '{print $1}' <<< $l_out)\";done.
