sca.check.id: 31160
sca.check.title: Ensure authselect includes with-faillock.
sca.check.description: The pam_faillock.so module maintains a list of failed authentication attempts per user during a specified interval and locks the account in case there were more than deny consecutive failed authentications. It stores the failure records into per-user files in the tally directory.
sca.check.rationale: Locking out user IDs after n unsuccessful consecutive login attempts mitigates brute force password attacks against your systems.
sca.check.remediation: Run the following commands to include the with-faillock option to the current authselect profile: # authselect enable-feature with-faillock # authselect apply-changes.
