sca.check.title: Ensure default group for the root account is GID 0.
sca.check.description: The usermod command can be used to specify which group the root account belongs to. This affects permissions of files that are created by the root account.
sca.check.rationale: Using GID 0 for the root account helps prevent root -owned files from accidentally becoming accessible to non-privileged users.
sca.check.remediation: Run the following command to set the root account default group to GID 0 : # usermod -g 0 root.
